# Client-side scheduling tool prototype (2026-01-15 00:01Z)

_**User (2026-01-15 00:01Z)**_

You are an expert front-end engineer. Build a **simple, desktop-first, client-side-only prototype** of a scheduling tool (Calendly-style) using:

- Plain HTML/CSS/JavaScript (no frameworks).
- Tailwind CSS via CDN.
- All logic client-side (no backend, no real calendar integrations).
- One page (index.html) with inline JS, or a small JS file if you prefer.

Goal:
Create a minimal scheduling flow (Variant A: “time first”) where a user can:

1. Choose a meeting type (Product demo or Technical deep dive).
2. Pick a date & time (time first) with a **toggle for two date selection modes**:
 - Monthly calendar view
 - “Upcoming available timeslots” list view
3. Enter minimal details.
4. See a confirmation with dummy “Add to calendar” buttons.

We want this **fast, simple, and desktop-oriented**. No authentication, no persistence, no real sending of emails.

Please build this in:
/Users/gwaldau/Cursor projects/scheduler tool

---

## High-Level UX / Layout

- **Desktop-first**:
- Use a centered layout with a max-width container (e.g. `max-w-5xl mx-auto`).
- The main scheduling step (Step 1) should be a **two-column layout** on desktop:
  - Left column (~40%): Title, subtitle, step indicator, meeting type selection, brief text.
  - Right column (~60%): Time zone information, view toggle (calendar vs list), date/time selection, primary CTA.
- **Responsive**:
- It should still behave reasonably on smaller screens (stacked columns), but the primary design is optimized for desktop widths (e.g. 1024px+).

---

## Functional Requirements

### Overall

- Single-page-like behavior: all steps live in one HTML file as separate sections or containers, shown/hidden by JS.
- Use Tailwind for styling (via CDN link in the `<head>`).
- Clean, legible desktop UI, but doesn’t need to be pixel-perfect.

### Steps (Variant A – Time First)

We have 3 main steps:

---

### Step 1: Choose meeting type & time (with view toggle)

**Layout**

- Left column:
- Page title: “Talk to our experts”
- Subtitle: “Book a product demo or technical deep dive with the Workday team.”
- A simple step indicator/stepper, e.g.:
  - `Step 1 of 3 — Choose time`
- Meeting type selection:
  - Two radio buttons:
    - Product demo (30 minutes)
    - Technical deep dive (60 minutes)
  - Default selection: Product demo.
  - Each may have a short description line.
- Optional short paragraph: “Pick a time in the next few days that works for you.”

- Right column:
- Time zone display:
  - Auto-detect user time zone using `Intl.DateTimeFormat().resolvedOptions().timeZone`.
  - Show a label like: `Time zone: America/Los_Angeles`.
  - Add a `<select>` dropdown with a few sample time zones (e.g., America/Los_Angeles, America/New_York, Europe/London). Changing it only updates the label; it does NOT need to adjust slot times logically.
- **View toggle** (important):
  - Two buttons or a segmented control at the top of the date/time module:
    - “Calendar view”
    - “Upcoming timeslots”
  - Default to **Calendar view** on initial load.
  - Clicking a toggle:
    - Sets an internal state variable like `viewMode = 'calendar'` or `viewMode = 'list'`.
    - Shows/hides the corresponding date/time selection UI.

---

#### Mode 1: Calendar view (monthly calendar)

In this mode, on the right column:

- A simple monthly calendar for the **current month**, showing days in a grid (7 columns for weekdays).
- You do NOT need to support navigating between months for this prototype; showing the current month is enough.
- Requirements:
- Display weekday headings (S, M, T, W, T, F, S).
- Layout days as a grid with Tailwind (e.g. `grid grid-cols-7 gap-1`).
- For simplicity, all days from today forward can be considered “bookable”.
- Visually differentiate:
  - Today (highlight or border).
  - Selected date (distinct highlight).
  - Past days (dimmed and non-clickable).
- When a user clicks on a valid day:
- Store that day as the selected date in state.
- Show a time slots area below the calendar for that chosen date.

**Time slots in Calendar view**:

- Below the calendar grid, render a section labeled like “Available times”.
- Show a grid/list of time buttons for the selected date, e.g.:

- Use a hard-coded array such as:
  ```js
  const TIME_SLOTS = ["9:00 AM", "9:30 AM", "10:00 AM", "10:30 AM", "11:00 AM", "2:00 PM", "2:30 PM", "3:00 PM"];

+                 } else if (isToday) {
+                     classes += 'bg-blue-50 text-blue-700 font-medium border-2 border-blue-300';
+                 } else {
+                     classes += 'text-gray-700 hover:bg-gray-100';
+                 }
+                 
+                 html += &#96;&lt;div class="${classes}" data-date="${date.toISOString()}" ${isPast ? '' : 'onclick="selectDate(this)"'}&gt;${day}&lt;/div&gt;&#96;;
+             }
+             
+             html += '&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;';
+             container.innerHTML = html;
+         }
+         
+         // Date selection handler
+         function selectDate(element) {
+             const dateStr = element.getAttribute('data-date');
+             state.selectedDate = dateStr;
+             state.selectedTime = null; // Reset time selection
+             
+             // Update visual selection
+             document.querySelectorAll('.calendar-day').forEach(day =&gt; {
+                 day.classList.remove('bg-blue-600', 'text-white', 'selected');
+                 if (!day.classList.contains('disabled')) {
+                     day.classList.add('text-gray-700');
+                 }
+             });
+             element.classList.add('bg-blue-600', 'text-white', 'selected');
+             element.classList.remove('text-gray-700', 'bg-blue-50', 'text-blue-700', 'border-2', 'border-blue-300');
+             
+             // Show time slots
+             showTimeSlots();
+             updateContinueButton();
+         }
+         
+         // Show time slots for selected date
+         function showTimeSlots() {
+             const container = document.getElementById('timeSlotsContainer');
+             const grid = document.getElementById('timeSlotsGrid');
+             
+             container.classList.remove('hidden');
+             
+             grid.innerHTML = TIME_SLOTS.map(time =&gt; {
+                 const isSelected = state.selectedTime === time;
+                 const classes = isSelected 
+                     ? 'time-slot bg-blue-600 text-white border-blue-600 selected'
+                     : 'time-slot bg-white text-gray-700 border-gray-300 hover:border-blue-500';
+                 
+                 return &#96;
+                     &lt;button class="${classes} border rounded-lg py-2 px-3 text-sm font-medium" 
+                             onclick="selectTime('${time}')"&gt;
+                         ${time}
+                     &lt;/button&gt;
+                 &#96;;
+             }).join('');
+         }
+         
+         // Time selection handler
+         function selectTime(time) {
+             state.selectedTime = time;
+             
+             // Update visual selection
+             document.querySelectorAll('.time-slot').forEach(slot =&gt; {
+                 slot.classList.remove('bg-blue-600', 'text-white', 'border-blue-600', 'selected');
+                 slot.classList.add('bg-white', 'text-gray-700', 'border-gray-300');
+             });
+             
+             event.target.classList.add('bg-blue-600', 'text-white', 'border-blue-600', 'selected');
+             event.target.classList.remove('bg-white', 'text-gray-700', 'border-gray-300');
+             
+             updateContinueButton();
+         }
+         
+         // Make selectTime available globally
+         window.selectTime = selectTime;
+         window.selectDate = selectDate;
+         
+         // Generate upcoming slots list view
+         function generateUpcomingSlotsList() {
+             const container = document.getElementById('upcomingSlotsList');
+             const now = new Date();
+             const slots = [];
+             
+             // Generate slots for next 7 days
+             for (let dayOffset = 0; dayOffset &lt; 7; dayOffset++) {
+                 const date = new Date(now);
+                 date.setDate(date.getDate() + dayOffset);
+                 date.setHours(0, 0, 0, 0);
+                 
+                 TIME_SLOTS.forEach(time =&gt; {
+                     slots.push({
+                         date: new Date(date),
+                         time: time,
+                         dateStr: date.toISOString()
+                     });
+                 });
+             }
+             
+             container.innerHTML = slots.map(slot =&gt; {
+                 const dateStr = slot.date.toLocaleDateString('en-US', { 
+                     weekday: 'long', 
+                     month: 'short', 
+                     day: 'numeric' 
+                 });
+                 const isSelected = state.selectedDate === slot.dateStr &amp;&amp; state.selectedTime === slot.time;
+                 const classes = isSelected
+                     ? 'p-4 border-2 border-blue-600 bg-blue-50 rounded-lg cursor-pointer'
+                     : 'p-4 border border-gray-300 rounded-lg cursor-pointer hover:border-blue-300 hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors';
+                 
+                 return &#96;
+                     &lt;div class="${classes}" onclick="selectSlotFromList('${slot.dateStr}', '${slot.time}')"&gt;
+                         &lt;div class="font-medium text-gray-900"&gt;${dateStr}&lt;/div&gt;
+                         &lt;div class="text-sm text-gray-600"&gt;${slot.time}&lt;/div&gt;
+                     &lt;/div&gt;
+                 &#96;;
+             }).join('');
+         }
+         
+         // Select slot from list view
+         function selectSlotFromList(dateStr, time) {
+             state.selectedDate = dateStr;
+             state.selectedTime = time;
+             
+             // Update visual selection
+             document.querySelectorAll('#upcomingSlotsList &gt; div').forEach(div =&gt; {
+                 div.classList.remove('border-blue-600', 'bg-blue-50', 'border-2');
+                 div.classList.add('border-gray-300', 'border');
+             });
+             
+             event.currentTarget.classList.add('border-blue-600', 'bg-blue-50', 'border-2');
+             event.currentTarget.classList.remove('border-gray-300');
+             
+             updateContinueButton();
+         }
+         
+         // Make selectSlotFromList available globally
+         window.selectSlotFromList = selectSlotFromList;
+         
+         // Update continue button state
+         function updateContinueButton() {
+             const btn = document.getElementById('continueBtn');
+             if (state.selectedDate &amp;&amp; state.selectedTime) {
+                 btn.disabled = false;
+             } else {
+                 btn.disabled = true;
+             }
+         }
+         
+         // Form validation for Step 2
+         function initializeFormValidation() {
+             const nameInput = document.getElementById('userName');
+             const emailInput = document.getElementById('userEmail');
+             const continueBtn = document.getElementById('continueToStep3Btn');
+             
+             function validateForm() {
+                 const name = nameInput.value.trim();
+                 const email = emailInput.value.trim();
+                 const emailValid = /^[^\s@]+@[^\s@]+\.[^\s@]+$/.test(email);
+                 
+                 if (name &amp;&amp; email &amp;&amp; emailValid) {
+                     continueBtn.disabled = false;
+                 } else {
+                     continueBtn.disabled = true;
+                 }
+             }
+             
+             nameInput.addEventListener('input', validateForm);
+             emailInput.addEventListener('input', validateForm);
+         }
+         
+         // Navigation between steps
+         function initializeNavigation() {
+             const continueBtn = document.getElementById('continueBtn');
+             const backToStep1Btn = document.getElementById('backToStep1Btn');
+             const continueToStep3Btn = document.getElementById('continueToStep3Btn');
+             
+             continueBtn.addEventListener('click', () =&gt; {
+                 showStep(2);
+             });
+             
+             backToStep1Btn.addEventListener('click', () =&gt; {
+                 showStep(1);
+             });
+             
+             continueToStep3Btn.addEventListener('click', () =&gt; {
+                 // Save form data
+                 state.userName = document.getElementById('userName').value.trim();
+                 state.userEmail = document.getElementById('userEmail').value.trim();
+                 state.userNotes = document.getElementById('userNotes').value.trim();
+                 
+                 // Update confirmation
+                 updateConfirmation();
+                 showStep(3);
+             });
+         }
+         
+         // Show specific step
+         function showStep(stepNumber) {
+             document.getElementById('step1').classList.toggle('hidden', stepNumber !== 1);
+             document.getElementById('step2').classList.toggle('hidden', stepNumber !== 2);
+             document.getElementById('step3').classList.toggle('hidden', stepNumber !== 3);
+         }
+         
+         // Update confirmation details
+         function updateConfirmation() {
+             const meetingTypeText = state.meetingType === 'demo' 
+                 ? 'Product demo (30 minutes)' 
+                 : 'Technical deep dive (60 minutes)';
+             
+             const selectedDate = new Date(state.selectedDate);
+             const dateStr = selectedDate.toLocaleDateString('en-US', { 
+                 weekday: 'long', 
+                 month: 'long', 
+                 day: 'numeric', 
+                 year: 'numeric' 
+             });
+             
+             document.getElementById('confirmMeetingType').textContent = meetingTypeText;
+             document.getElementById('confirmDateTime').textContent = &#96;${dateStr} at ${state.selectedTime}&#96;;
+             document.getElementById('confirmTimezone').textContent = state.timezone;
+             document.getElementById('confirmName').textContent = state.userName;
+             document.getElementById('confirmEmail').textContent = state.userEmail;
+         }
+     &lt;/script&gt;
+ &lt;/body&gt;
+ &lt;/html&gt;
+

Built a desktop-first scheduling tool prototype. Summary:

## Features implemented

### Step 1: Choose meeting type & time
- Two-column layout (40% left, 60% right)
- Left column: Title, subtitle, step indicator, meeting type selection (Product demo / Technical deep dive)
- Right column: Time zone (auto-detected with dropdown), view toggle, date/time selection

### View toggle
- Calendar view (default): Monthly calendar grid showing the current month
  - Highlights today
  - Past days are disabled
  - Clicking a date shows time slots below
  - Time slots displayed as clickable buttons
- Upcoming timeslots view: List of available slots for the next 7 days
  - Shows date and time for each slot
  - Clickable to select

### Additional steps
- Step 2: Enter details (name, email, optional notes)
- Step 3: Confirmation with dummy "Add to calendar" buttons

### Technical details
- Plain HTML/CSS/JavaScript (no frameworks)
- Tailwind CSS via CDN
- Fully client-side (no backend)
- Desktop-first responsive design
- State management for selections
- Form validation

Open `index.html` in a browser to use it. The calendar shows the current month, and you can toggle between calendar and list views to select a time slot.
